The paper deals with the notion of generalized weights for rank metric codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of polymatroids and demi-polymatroids is a common technique in coding theory (cs.DS) and the paper explicitly mentions the connection between these concepts and linear codes. The paper also discusses duality, which is a topic in optimization and graph theory (cs.SI). The use of weights and their properties is a common topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
